James de Villiers, News24NSRI Kommetjie and NSRI Simonstown in attendance at the fishing vessel Maria Louisa off-shore of Cape Point. (NSRI) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; Sea rescue teams are searching for a fisherman who fell from a vessel near Cape Point on Wednesday morning, the NSRI said.The 43-year-old went overboard as the Maria Louisa was motoring toward fishing grounds, National Sea Rescue Institute Kommetjie station commander Ian Klopper said in a statement.The reason why he fell overboard was unclear. The vessel was two nautical miles, roughly 3.7km, from Cape Point when the crew realised he was missing.An NSRI rescue swimmer, a Western Cape emergency services rescue diver, and a Skymed rescue helicopter were looking for him, along with the Maria Louisa and a private boat.By Wednesday afternoon there was no trace of him. Ships in the area had been alerted to keep a lookout.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.